<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-03-04T23:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-03-04T23:00:00-05:00" n="549" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d549">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/4576: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in Switzerland (<persName corresp="#p_WHR1" type="to">Wilson</persName>), at Geneva</hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-03-04T23:00:00-05:00">March 4, 1932—11
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>27. Your 52, March 4, 6 p.m., and 53, March 4, 9 p.m.</p>
                        <p>Have telegraphed Shanghai requesting that American military authorities
                            cooperate. Inform <persName corresp="#p_DSE1">Drummond</persName>.</p>
                        <closer><signed><persName corresp="#p_SHL1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>